FBIS3-51194 "drlat010_c_94005" FBIS-LAT-94-010 Document Type:Daily Report 14 Jan 1994 MEXICO Chiapas Crisis Defense Secretariat Reports `Complete Calm' PA1401015694 Mexico City Radio ACIR Network in Spanish 0030 GMT 14 Jan 94 PA1401015694 Mexico City Radio ACIR Network Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [Report by Jesus Cazasola; from the "Vector 21" newscast] [Text] The National Defense Secretariat reported that in compliance with presidential orders, troops operating in upper Chiapas State to counter action by law breakers have concentrated in the villages or towns of Rancho Nuevo, San Cristobal de las Casas, Ocosingo, Altamirano, near Las Margaritas, Comitan, Chanal, San Juan Chamula, and Tuxtla Gutierrez, Chiapas State. The military personnel continue to perform social work in some of these communities, especially water and food distribution chores, as well as the distribution of other primary articles. The Mexican Army soldiers continue to patrol the various communities to prevent possible attacks on the residents. Up to now no armed group has been seen. The National Defense Secretariat report concludes by stating that there is complete calm.
